### 6. Model Existence Checks (404 for Missing Source)

**Function**: `getExistingName()` (lines 1031-1053)

This function performs case-insensitive model name matching against existing manifests:

```go
func getExistingName(n model.Name) (model.Name, error) {
    var zero model.Name
    // Get all existing manifests from disk
    existing, err := manifest.Manifests(true)
    if err != nil {
        return zero, err
    }

    var set model.Name // tracks parts already canonicalized

    // Case-insensitive prefix matching on:
    // - Host (registry)
    // - Namespace
    // - Model name
    // - Tag
    for e := range existing {
        if set.Host == "" && strings.EqualFold(e.Host, n.Host) {
            n.Host = e.Host
        }
        if set.Namespace == "" && strings.EqualFold(e.Namespace, n.Namespace) {
            n.Namespace = e.Namespace
        }
        if set.Model == "" && strings.EqualFold(e.Model, n.Model) {
            n.Model = e.Model
        }
        if set.Tag == "" && strings.EqualFold(e.Tag, n.Tag) {
            n.Tag = e.Tag
        }
    }
    return n, nil
}
```

